
@chapter Introduction

This manual documents the Lambda LISP machine networking software
that is distributed with Release 4.0
of the ZetaLISP-Plus@tm@ system software.@footnote[Hereafter referred to simply as @ii(Release 4)]

Before reading this manual, review the @i(Lambda 4.0 LISP Release Notes),
which documents new features of the Release 4 software.
That manual also documents the procedure for installing Release 4.

@section Networking Release Notes

Part I of this manual, entitled @b(Networking Release Notes),
describes changes to the networking software
in terms of @ii(functionality), @ii(installation), @ii(configuration), and @ii(operating procedures).
The following chapters are included:

@itemize @bullet
@item @nameref[chapter-architecture]  [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-architecture])]
@item @nameref[chapter-installation]  [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-installation])]
@item @nameref[chapter-configuration] [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-configuration])]
@item @nameref[chapter-operating]     [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-operating])]
@item @nameref[chapter-tcp-app]       [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-tcp-app])]
@item @nameref[chapter-limitations]   [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-limitations])]
@end(itemize)

Prior to installing Release 4,
the Lambda system manager should review the information contained in this section.

@sp 1

@textbox @b(Note:)
To provide properly functioning networking software,
you (or the Lambda system manager at your site)
@i(must) read this manual carefully and
perform the required site file configuration and installation.

The phrase ``site files,'' used frequently in this manual,
refers to the static network configuration information that is entered in files
located in your @l("SYS:SITE;") directory.
@end(textbox)

@section Networking Guide

Part II of this manual, entitled @b(Networking Guide),
provides comprehensive documentation on LISP networking software.
The chapters in Part II include new information
as well as information gathered from earlier manuals:

@itemize @bullet
@item @nameref[chapter-doc-architecture]  [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-doc-architecture])]
@item @nameref[chapter-doc-configuration] [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-doc-configuration])]
@item @nameref[chapter-doc-operating]     [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-doc-operating])]
@item @nameref[chapter-doc-generic-applications] [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-doc-generic-applications])]
@item @nameref[chapter-doc-tcp-app]       [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-doc-tcp-app])]
@item @nameref[chapter-doc-chaos-app]     [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-doc-chaos-app])]
@item @nameref[chapter-doc-programs]      [Chapter @i(@ref[chapter-doc-programs])]
@end(itemize)

Experienced Lambda system managers may be able to make the necessary
configuration changes after reading
the release notes.
Others (including system managers with new Lambda systems) should read
Chapter @ref[chapter-doc-configuration], @b(@nameref[chapter-doc-configuration]),
which documents the configuration process.

Users of previous releases should read
Chapter @ref[chapter-operating], @b[@nameref(chapter-operating)]
for information on functionality that has changed.
Complete operating information is provided in
Chapter @ref[chapter-doc-operating], @b(@nameref[chapter-doc-operating]),
and subsequent chapters.

@section Appendices

Part III of this manual contains supplementary material on various topics.

Appendix @ref[appendix-systypes], @b(@nameref[appendix-systypes]),
documents the currently supported network host types.
Each host flavor is listed, along with its related attributes
(such as the keywords that determine a host's machine and system type).

Appendix @ref[appendix-unix], @b(@nameref[appendix-unix]),
documents selected features of the LMI System 5 Unix Chaosnet software,
which is provided with Lambda-Plus systems.










